[32m╭─[0m[32m───────────────────────────────[0m[32m [0m[1;32mLLM Response[0m[32m [0m[32m───────────────────────────────[0m[32m─╮[0m
[32m│[0m I'll help you craft the curl command for POSTing to /login with form data    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m and capturing session cookies. Here's how to do it:                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```bash                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m curl -X POST "http://target/login" \                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   -d "username=test&password=test" \                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   -v -i                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **What each flag does:**                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `-X POST`: Specifies POST method                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `-d "username=test&password=test"`: Sends form data                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `-v`: Verbose output (shows request/response headers including Set-Cookie) [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `-i`: Includes response headers in output                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **To automatically save the session cookie:**                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```bash                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m curl -X POST "http://target/login" \                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   -d "username=test&password=test" \                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   -v -i \                                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   -c cookies.txt                                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Then use the cookie in subsequent requests:**                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```bash                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m curl -b cookies.txt "http://target/dashboard"                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Example output you'll see:**                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m * Trying 127.0.0.1:80...                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m * Connected to target (127.0.0.1) port 80 (#0)                               [32m│[0m
